<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 2:27PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Heavy showers will impact portions of west central Appomattox,
central Campbell and central Pittsylvania Counties through 300 PM
EDT...
At 225 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking heavy showers along a line
extending from near Hodges to near Swansonville. Movement was
northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Torrential downpours and winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Ponding of water and poor drainage flooding can impact
travel. Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Gretna...
Hodges...
Climax...
Gladys...
Spout Spring...
Swansonville...
and Oakville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
